<p><img alt="Student Studying" height="250" src="Images/Admin_Offices/Online Learning/OD/TaylerJaromPrice.jpg" title="Price Family Studying" width="710" /></p>
<p>BYU-Idaho's Online Degree programs allow former students of BYU-Idaho and Ricks College, BYU, BYU-Hawaii, and LDS Business College to finish their degree even though they have moved away from campus.</p>
<h3>Online Degree Program Admission Qualifications:</h3>
<ol start="1" type="1">
<li>Be in good academic and financial standing at all institutions previously attended.</li>
<li>Have completed a minimum of 15 credits from Ricks College, BYU-Idaho, LDS Business College or BYU-Hawaii. If you accumulated a total of 15 credits from attending two or more of these institutions (but did not accumulate 15 at one particular institution), you may still qualify. (<strong>Note:</strong> These 15 credits must be earned in physical, on-campus studies, not through online or distance programs. You may also earn these 15 credits through the BYU-Idaho Pathway program. Learn more <a href="x21541.xml">here</a> and see if there is a Pathway <a href="x46402.xml">location</a> near you.)</li>
<li>Have a total cumulative grade point average (GPA) of 2.5 or higher on previous college study. (If you are a former full-time student of Ricks College or BYU-Idaho and have not attended any other college/university since last attending Ricks/BYU-Idaho, you may be eligible for admission with a cumulative GPA of 2.0 or higher.)</li>
<li>Be in good financial standing at all institutions previously attended.</li>
<li>Commit to the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/catalog/2012-2013/University%20Standards.pdf">BYU-Idaho Honor Code</a> and maintain annual ecclesiastical endorsements.</li>
</ol><ol></ol>
<h3>Required Application Materials</h3>
<ol>
<li>Part 1 - Student Information</li>
<li>Part 2 - School Selection</li>
<li>Part 3 - Student Commitment &amp; Ecclesiastical Endorsement</li>
</ol>
<p>* An application fee will be assessed during the first semester of Online Degree enrollment for students who have not previously paid the fee to BYU-Idaho.</p>
<ol></ol>
